
---


@startuml

' GameArea has a name and contains GameElements and GamePieces
class GameArea {
    name: String
}

' GameElement has x and y coordinates
class GameElement {
    x: long
    y: long
}

' Shape extends GameElement
class Shape {}

' Object extends GameElement
class Object {}

' Opponent extends GameElement
class Opponent {
    lives: int
    kill()
}

' Boss is a special type of Opponent known to GameArea
class Boss {
    lives: int
    kill()
}

' GamePiece is not detailed in inheritance, just used for composition
class GamePiece {}

' Relationships

' A GameArea consists of multiple GameElements (1 or more)
GameArea "1" o-- "1..*" GameElement : contains

' A GameArea consists of 1 or 2 GamePieces
GameArea "1" o-- "1..2" GamePiece : contains

' A GameElement can be a Shape, Object, or Opponent
GameElement <|-- Shape
GameElement <|-- Object
GameElement <|-- Opponent

' An Opponent can be a Boss (only one per GameArea)
GameArea "1" --> "1" Boss : knowsAsBoss

' Shapes can be connected to any number of other Shapes
Shape "0..*" -- "0..*" Shape : connectsTo

@enduml

---

### 🧾 Explanation of Key Elements:

- **`GameArea`**:
  - Has a `name`.
  - Composes at least one `GameElement` and 1–2 `GamePiece`s.
  - Knows exactly one `Boss`.

- **`GameElement`**:
  - Base class with `x` and `y` position values.
  - Extended by `Shape`, `Object`, and `Opponent`.

- **`Shape`**:
  - Can connect to zero or more other shapes via an association.

- **`Opponent`**:
  - Has `lives` and a `kill()` method.
  - Specialized as `Boss` in the `GameArea`.

- **`GamePiece`**:
  - Not extended; simply part of the game area’s composition.

